**Conclusion.**  
The dihedral angles of the tetrahedron evolve according to a constrained overdamped Langevin equation in which two time‑dependent Lagrange multipliers enforce (i) exact volume conservation and (ii) the geometric constraint \(\sum_{i<j}\cos\theta_{ij}\,\ell_{ij}^{2}=0\).  In explicit form  

\[
\boxed{
\dot{\theta}_{ij}(t)=
-\,\frac{\partial U}{\partial\theta_{ij}}
-\mu(t)\,\frac{\partial C_{V}}{\partial\theta_{ij}}
-\lambda(t)\,\frac{\partial C_{A}}{\partial\theta_{ij}}
+\eta_{ij}(t)
}
\qquad (i<j,\;i,j=1,\dots ,4)
\]

with  

\[
U[\{\theta\}]=\kappa\sum_{i<j}\sin^{2}\theta_{ij}\;\;\Longrightarrow\;\;
\frac{\partial U}{\partial\theta_{ij}}=2\kappa\sin\theta_{ij}\cos\theta_{ij},
\]

\[
C_{V}\equiv V(t)-V_{0}
= \frac{\sqrt{2}}{12}\sum_{i<j}\sin\theta_{ij}\,\ell_{ij}^{3}-V_{0}
\;\;\Longrightarrow\;\;
\frac{\partial C_{V}}{\partial\theta_{ij}}
=\frac{\sqrt{2}}{12}\,\ell_{ij}^{3}\cos\theta_{ij},
\]

\[
C_{A}\equiv\sum_{i<j}\cos\theta_{ij}\,\ell_{ij}^{2}=0
\;\;\Longrightarrow\;\;
\frac{\partial C_{A}}{\partial\theta_{ij}}
=-\sin\theta_{ij}\,\ell_{ij}^{2}
+\cos\theta_{ij}\,\frac{\partial\ell_{ij}^{2}}{\partial\theta_{ij}}
\equiv -\sin\theta_{ij}\,\ell_{ij}^{2}
+\cos\theta_{ij}\,g_{ij}(\theta_{ij}),
\]

where the chord length on the unit‑radius 3‑sphere is  

\[
\ell_{ij}=2\sin\!\Bigl(\frac{\psi_{ij}}{2}\Bigr),\qquad 
\cos\psi_{ij}= \frac{\cos\theta_{ij}+ \cos^{2}\theta_{ij}}{1+\cos\theta_{ij}},
\]

so that \(g_{ij}(\theta_{ij})=\partial_{\theta_{ij}}\ell_{ij}^{2}\) is a known analytic function of \(\theta_{ij}\).

The Lagrange multipliers are obtained at each instant by imposing \(\dot C_{V}=0\) and \(\dot C_{A}=0\):

\[
\begin{pmatrix}
A_{VV} & A_{VA}\\[2pt]
A_{AV} & A_{AA}
\end{pmatrix}
\begin{pmatrix}
\mu\\ \lambda
\end{pmatrix}
=
\begin{pmatrix}
B_{V}\\[2pt]
B_{A}
\end{pmatrix},
\]

with  

\[
\begin{aligned}
A_{VV}&=\sum_{i<j}\!\left(\frac{\sqrt{2}}{12}\,\ell_{ij}^{3}\cos\theta_{ij}\right)^{2},\\[4pt]
A_{VA}=A_{AV}&=\sum_{i<j}\!\frac{\sqrt{2}}{12}\,\ell_{ij}^{3}\cos\theta_{ij}
\Bigl[-\sin\theta_{ij}\,\ell_{ij}^{2}+\cos\theta_{ij}\,g_{ij}\Bigr],\\[4pt]
A_{AA}&=\sum_{i<j}\!\Bigl[-\sin\theta_{ij}\,\ell_{ij}^{2}+\cos\theta_{ij}\,g_{ij}\Bigr]^{2},\\[6pt]
B_{V}&=\sum_{i<j}\frac{\sqrt{2}}{12}\,\ell_{ij}^{3}\cos\theta_{ij}
\Bigl[2\kappa\sin\theta_{ij}\cos\theta_{ij}-\eta_{ij}\Bigr],\\[4pt]
B_{A}&=\sum_{i<j}\Bigl[-\sin\theta_{ij}\,\ell_{ij}^{2}+\cos\theta_{ij}\,g_{ij}\Bigr]
\Bigl[2\kappa\sin\theta_{ij}\cos\theta_{ij}-\eta_{ij}\Bigr].
\end{aligned}
\]

Solving this \(2\times2\) linear system yields \(\mu(t)\) and \(\lambda(t)\) as explicit (but noise‑dependent) functions of the instantaneous configuration \(\{\theta_{ij},\ell_{ij}\}\).  

The stochastic forcing \(\eta_{ij}(t)\) is Gaussian white noise with  

\[
\langle\eta_{ij}(t)\eta_{kl}(t')\rangle=\sigma^{2}\,\delta_{ik}\,\delta_{jl}\,\delta(t-t').
\]

Because the multipliers are chosen to satisfy \(\dot C_{V}=0\) and \(\dot C_{A}=0\), the volume \(V(t)\) remains exactly constant and the auxiliary constraint is preserved for all \(t\), provided they hold at the initial regular tetrahedron  

\[
\theta_{ij}(0)=\arccos(-1/3),\qquad \ell_{ij}(0)=\ell_{0}.
\]

Thus the boxed equation together with the definitions above constitutes the exact non‑linear stochastic differential equation governing the time evolution of the tetrahedral dihedral angles under the stipulated physical and geometric constraints.
